    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "A student wants to draw a shape using a randomly generated color. Each color is created by randomly selecting red, green, and blue values from 0 to 255.\r\n\r\n✅ <strong>TO DO:</strong> In <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; font-weight: bold;\">ShapeScene.java</code>, complete the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; font-weight: bold;\">makeRandomColor()</code> method. It should:\r\n\r\n1. Generate three numbers between 0 and 255.\r\n2. Use those numbers to create and return a new <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; font-weight: bold;\">Color</code> object.\r\n\r\n✅ <strong>TO DO:</strong> In <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; font-weight: bold;\">TheaterRunner.java</code>, call <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; font-weight: bold;\">makeRandomColor()</code> and use it to draw a shape.\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background-color: #E0D1EC; border: 1px solid #9660bf; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 1.1em; padding: 15px;\">\r\n💡 <strong>TIP:</strong> Use <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; font-weight: bold;\">new Color(r, g, b)</code> to create a color from red, green, and blue values.\r\n</div>\r\n",
